CBOE Volatility Index (VIX)

Real time data on CBOE Volatility Index (VIX Index) - indexcboe: vix. CBOE stands for Chicago Board Options Exchange, which calculates the implied volatility of the S&P 500 index options, and represents the monthly expectations of stock market behavior. You will find more information by going to one of the tab-sections on this page for live and historical data, charts, technical analysis and more. Visit the "Forum" section for discussions, recent sentiments and rankings by our users.

chat gpt: You can actually apply divergence to the VIX index as well. The idea is that when the VIX, which measures market volatility, moves in one direction while the underlying market or another indicator moves in the opposite direction, it can signal a potential change in market sentiment. So, just like with price and RSI, you can look for divergences between the VIX and the market to predict potential shifts.
